# flame-core MAP

Wayfinding for a cold-start session. See `CLAUDE.md` (this directory) for hard
rules and `docs/FLAME_README.md` for the docs index. This file is the
"where does X live" cheat sheet.

## 1. Entry points

- Library root: `src/lib.rs`. Re-exports: `Tensor`, `TensorId`, `DType`,
  `Device`, `Shape`, `Error`/`Result`, `Parameter` (alias `Var`),
  `GradientMap`, `AutogradContext`, `Op`, `Module` trait, `nn::{Linear,
  Conv2d, LayerNorm, Embedding, AdamW}`. Auto-runs `init()` via `#[ctor]`
  (reads `FLAME_DEFAULT_DTYPE`, `FLAME_FORCE_CUDNN`).
- Crate version: `26.15.1`. Pinned by `EriDiffusion-v2` with `version =
  "=26.15.1"` — bumping breaks trainers.
- Downstream crates:
  - `inference-flame` — features `["cuda","bf16_u16","cudnn","shared_storage"]`.
  - `EriDiffusion-v2` — trainers (Klein, Z-Image, Chroma, Qwen, Anima, …).
- C API: `src/capi.rs` (feature `capi`, off by default). Python bindings:
  `src/python/` (feature `python`, off by default).

